CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 22, 1947, pg. 29, reads: "Hill District Landscape - One of artist Harry W. Scheuch's two paintings that was awarded the $200 Carnegie Institute prize for best group 2 oil paintings. The canvas is hung in the Carnegie Institute Art Gallery as par of the current thirty-seventh annual exhibition of the Associated Artists of Pittsburgh. The show will last until March 13. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Painting by Harry Scheuch of people selecting evergreen trees in urban lot, with label underneath reading "Carnegie Institute Prize" at Associated Artists of Pittsburgh exhibition in Carnegie Institute (Carnegie Museum of Art)
